In this press gaggle, Principal Deputy Press Secretary Josh Earnest announces that President Obama will be departing Martha's Vineyard this evening to return to the White House. He also provides an update on the preparations for Hurricane Irene, including a conference call with Chief of Staff Bill Daley, DHS Secretary Janet Napolitano, and FEMA Administrator Craig Fugate. Earnest mentions that the Obama administration conducted a national-level exercise in 2009 to prepare for emergency situations, including a simulation of a category 3 hurricane striking New York City. He also notes that the President received an in-person briefing on the first day of hurricane season this year, with North Carolina Governor Perdue participating. Earnest emphasizes that the President is focused on ensuring the coordination between the federal government and local and state officials and that all available resources are being brought to bear on the hurricane response.